    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 27,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 685.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In view of the sentence from your telegram
                            of the 19th instant, asking, “If you can spare another, send a vessel to
                            Smyrna, to go thence <pb facs="0622" n="1356" xml:id="pg_1356"/>
                            wherever needed,” which I quoted to the Secretary of the Navy on the
                            20th instant, I have now to apprise you of the receipt of Mr. Herbert’s
                            reply of the 23d, observing that the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Minneapolis</hi> should sail for Smyrna on the 27th instant, and
                            that, allowing for delay of three days at Gibraltar for coal, this
                            vessel should reach her destination on or about the 14th proximo.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
